<paragraph id="6257336A793F0EDB1F5AAD0183DF21B5" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Frosch-Simse</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="E8DE0FF76DC59FDE7AE93284B0C98FCC" pageId="null" pageNumber="505" type="description">
<paragraph id="CF8DB6F69DA7442D7EBD43C77676898C" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="31F2443DBA53C6D63E3651A70028D842" class="Liliopsida" family="Juncaceae" genus="Juncus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="505" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bufonius">
<emphasis id="BD3920349663E97859112933953831A0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">J. bufonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 7a) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="495A2960965F369A0B312345D9142C2D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">
<normalizedToken id="2AADCD9610A16CE5FBE1F25260B0BCBB" originalValue="Grundständige" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Grundstaendige</normalizedToken>
Blattscheiden dunkelrot; innere 
<normalizedToken id="8DDE2F6F596195A8131C1320F019C498" originalValue="Perigonblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Perigonblaetter</normalizedToken>
meist stumpf, mit breitem, 
<normalizedToken id="C35FA6E51D20F57722A9FB67ABF5D825" originalValue="häutigem" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">haeutigem</normalizedToken>
Rand, oft 
<normalizedToken id="1AC6262DF8E869B16002BFAB6C17CE08" originalValue="kürzer" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">kuerzer</normalizedToken>
als die reife Frucht
</emphasis>
. - 
<normalizedToken id="D1C04E47F526724383700FC42571D72E" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: 
<normalizedToken id="A58848D5A5041AFADFC317D91312D844" originalValue="Später" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Spaeter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="C901CF1D31943433ED9009D5DEF77D73" originalValue="Frühling" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Fruehling</normalizedToken>
bis Herbst.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5CE9205B8538CEC093E0D1948CD70963" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">
<emphasis id="0AC90BCB2102BB4DEFB7BC45523830F3" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="0E8B9CFEE30BE1A07AEBA9D4D8766D1C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">30:</emphasis>
Material aus 
<normalizedToken id="CDE56B6829F9A07B3A16B5489E820CDF" originalValue="Grönland" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Groenland</normalizedToken>
(
<normalizedToken id="17F908474F270B0108B91F65518BF958" originalValue="Jörgensen" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Joergensen</normalizedToken>
et al. 1958). 
<emphasis id="4AE788436639C4DA31C9AD11FCD68E2E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">2n ca. 120:</emphasis>
Material aus Schleswig-Holstein (Wulff 1937a), aus Island (
<normalizedToken id="E820B0698E0772864240993FE2652110" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Loeve</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="93BFE061E41C2F8B6A72B05EA756D2FA" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Loeve</normalizedToken>
1956b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="163E6E095948407DD22F29933FF50E64" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">
<emphasis id="BB40C8CC3B004305FB075839B102A5A0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Standort.</emphasis>
Wie 
<emphasis id="53496563427D725DAB2E5E744C9BDD01" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">J. tenageja</emphasis>
(Nr. 6).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="31A224D45FD732F6E2D29FCD8ACBCC9F" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">
<emphasis id="BAC1A3DC44A3FC3B0CE3D123FEBD6DC0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">
<pageBreakToken id="7AEEA228E6B7E39AF3AA296A32FA5842" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Verbreitung</pageBreakToken>
</emphasis>
(
<normalizedToken id="47FF7AEED123804F009F65026842AC92" originalValue="ungenügend" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">ungenuegend</normalizedToken>
bekannt). 
<emphasis id="A4687ADF1E8E9BA0F65E03A54BEAE707" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">
<normalizedToken id="74F3B980656D2575A2C06729BBCA61AB" originalValue="Europäisch-nordamerikanische" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Europaeisch-nordamerikanische</normalizedToken>
Pflanze:
</emphasis>
Ganz 
<taxonomicName id="1DE5FE5BB3E1318DFE513FA5971919D1" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="505" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa</taxonomicName>
; Nordamerika; 
<normalizedToken id="4758249FF61E55B3CDCCFFA56CD3E6F6" originalValue="Grönland" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Groenland</normalizedToken>
. - Im Gebiet: Savoyen, 
<normalizedToken id="DC1A6216C7A49DAA214BE98D9188B0D9" originalValue="östliches" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">oestliches</normalizedToken>
Mittelland, 
<normalizedToken id="515AD098BCC46DC8FC40A54FC79D5AC4" originalValue="südliches" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">suedliches</normalizedToken>
Tessin (siehe Bemerkungen).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8DE9B4FA722196B0885340C2E730A65" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">
<emphasis id="6AB23B7F3534A6B9760885539DEF28C9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Bemerkungen.</emphasis>
Typischer 
<taxonomicName id="C65E42A191FB35670FDCE80FED5DFC41" class="Liliopsida" family="Juncaceae" genus="Juncus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="505" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ranarius">
<emphasis id="27364A0E576AC2671EBC0F53E5AA0255" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">J. ranarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
scheint im Gebiet nicht vorzukommen: Die innern 
<normalizedToken id="4A45C2763B368EC9E846699CC86C4100" originalValue="Perigonblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Perigonblaetter</normalizedToken>
sind nur bei einzelnen 
<normalizedToken id="4FDC87F15B0C44237983173466359EDA" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">Blueten</normalizedToken>
stumpf; es 
<normalizedToken id="D5DC5164F2670D4DF271E2CDB821F1FB" originalValue="könnte" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">koennte</normalizedToken>
sich um Bastarde zwischen 
<taxonomicName id="E3314C7591793E4DB7B23D8AD1B4DDA9" class="Liliopsida" family="Juncaceae" genus="Juncus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="505" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bufonius">
<emphasis id="101C796BA1EBD2BAC69865F2C958C71E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">J. bufonius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
und 
<taxonomicName id="6244A4942369FDF2E71C8FAAE71F2203" class="Liliopsida" family="Juncaceae" genus="Juncus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="505" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ranarius">
<emphasis id="86AE2D1B0F3144E89E9017D102A6156B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="505">J. ranarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
handeln.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
